## Introduction

This project is a Django-based web application designed to automate migration notifications to Slack channels. It leverages Django's ORM and migration framework to track database changes and sends real-time notifications to specified Slack workspaces. 

---

## Prerequisites

Ensure you have the following installed before proceeding:

1. [Python 3.x](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
2. [pip](https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/) (Python package installer)
3. [Virtualenv](https://virtualenv.pypa.io/en/stable/) (recommended for isolated Python environments)
4. [Git](https://git-scm.com/) (for version control)

---

## Installation

### Step 1: Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/shri123sharma/Slack_Migration_Notification_Project.git
```

### Step 2: Set Up a Virtual Environment
```bash
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows use `venv\Scripts\activate`
```

### Step 3: Install Dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### Step 4: Configure Environment Variables
```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

### Step 5: Apply Migrations
```bash
python manage.py migrate
```

### Step 6: Start the Development Server
```bash
python manage.py runserver
```

The server will start at http://127.0.0.1:8000/ by default. Open this URL in your web browser to access the app.


